{
  "description": "Codec conformance vectors for EMBEDDED VALUES in the node contract — gates kanonak-codec 0.2.0 (see kanonak-protocol/runtime#1). Ports implementing the 0.1.0 contract do not run this file. Wire shape: an embedded value is a map with no $id, an optional $name (the authored dict-key; hash-relevant), an optional $type (emits a type statement when present), and schema-mapped fields; field mapping without $type uses the containing object property's `range` (the 0.2.0 schema addition). Expected values are authoritative; canonical serialization of embedded values is additionally pinned by the ref-and-embedded case in kanonak-canonical/vectors.",
